-- Telefonica's Czech Unit to Cut 10% of Workforce This Year
-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 2013-01-21T14:51:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-21/telefonica-s-czech-unit-to-cut-10-of-workforce-this-year.html
Telefonica Czech Republic AS (SPTT) , the
country’s largest phone company, plans to reduce its workforce
10 percent this year to lower costs.  The details of the plan are still being worked out, the
Prague-based unit of Spain’s  Telefonica SA (TEF)  said in an e-mailed
statement today.  Telefonica cut its workforce 7.5% last year to 5,862 at the
end of December.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague at 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  